    <text>
    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Aug 21<hi rend="superscript">st</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Spencer</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am very much obliged to you for having so kindly sent me your Descriptive Sociology.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I saw some time ago some specimen sheets, &amp; was astonished at the amount of labour bestowed on the subject. How you find time passes my comprehension.</p>
<p>Yours sincerely obliged | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the reference to Spencer 1873a (see n. 2, below).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD evidently received a pre-publication copy of <hi rend="italic">Descriptive sociology</hi> (Spencer 1873a); the book was published in September (<hi rend="italic">Publishers’ Circular</hi>, 2 October 1873, p. 669). CD’s copy is in the Darwin Library–Down.</note>
        </div>        
            
